      "CVE": "CVE-2026-11352",
      "Description": "An issue in curl's QUIC UDP receive function allows a malicious HTTP/3 server\nto trigger a remote denial of service against a curl or libcurl client.\nBecause the helper function discards zero-length UDP datagrams before counting\nthem toward the per-call packet budget, a connected QUIC peer can continuously\nstream empty datagrams to indefinitely stall the client.",
      "Threats": [
        {
          "Type": "Impact",
          "Severity": "moderate"
        }
      ],
      "References": [
